# Companion workers for NVIDIA Brev (and any nvidia-container-toolkit host).
#
# Pick ONE of the 3 profiles below based on your GPU VRAM, then uncomment that
# block and `cp .env.brev.example .env.brev`. Or let `scripts/brev-bootstrap.sh`
# detect VRAM via nvidia-smi and pick a profile for you.
#
# Required vars after picking a profile:
#   LLM_IMAGE, LLM_START_COMMAND, LLM_HOST_PORT, LLM_MODEL
#   TTS_IMAGE, TTS_START_COMMAND, TTS_HOST_PORT, TTS_API_PATH, TTS_LANGUAGE, TTS_VOICE

# === PROFILE: low (≤8 GB VRAM — e.g. laptop RTX 3050 6GB, Brev T4) ===
# STT (large-v3 int8_float16) ~2.8 GB + llama.cpp 3B Q4_K_M ~2.5 GB + Piper CPU.
# Round-trip turn ~3 s. Good for local validation before Brev spend.
#
# LLM_IMAGE=ghcr.io/ggerganov/llama.cpp:server-cuda
# LLM_CONTAINER_PORT=8080
# LLM_HOST_PORT=8080
# LLM_MODEL=Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-Q4_K_M
# LLM_START_COMMAND=/llama-server --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 -hf bartowski/Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-GGUF:Q4_K_M --n-gpu-layers 99 --ctx-size 4096
#
# TTS_IMAGE=rhasspy/wyoming-piper:latest
# TTS_CONTAINER_PORT=10200
# TTS_HOST_PORT=8001
# TTS_API_PATH=/api/tts
# TTS_LANGUAGE=en
# TTS_VOICE=en_US-amy-medium
# TTS_START_COMMAND=python -m wyoming_piper --uri tcp://0.0.0.0:10200 --voice en_US-amy-medium

# === PROFILE: mid (8–16 GB VRAM — Brev L4, A10) ===
# STT large-v3 + Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-AWQ via vLLM (~6 GB) + Piper CPU.
# AWQ requires Ampere+. Round-trip turn <2 s.
#
# LLM_IMAGE=vllm/vllm-openai:latest
# LLM_CONTAINER_PORT=8080
# LLM_HOST_PORT=8080
# LLM_MODEL=Qwen/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-AWQ
# LLM_START_COMMAND=python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model Qwen/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-AWQ --port 8080 --gpu-memory-utilization 0.85 --max-model-len 8192
#
# TTS_IMAGE=rhasspy/wyoming-piper:latest
# TTS_CONTAINER_PORT=10200
# TTS_HOST_PORT=8001
# TTS_API_PATH=/api/tts
# TTS_LANGUAGE=en
# TTS_VOICE=en_US-amy-medium
# TTS_START_COMMAND=python -m wyoming_piper --uri tcp://0.0.0.0:10200 --voice en_US-amy-medium

# === PROFILE: high (≥16 GB VRAM — Brev A100, H100, B200) ===
# STT large-v3 + Qwen 7B AWQ + XTTS streaming (voice cloning, ~4 GB).
# Lowest latency, full quality. Round-trip <1.5 s.
#
# LLM_IMAGE=vllm/vllm-openai:latest
# LLM_CONTAINER_PORT=8080
# LLM_HOST_PORT=8080
# LLM_MODEL=Qwen/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-AWQ
# LLM_START_COMMAND=python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server --model Qwen/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-AWQ --port 8080 --gpu-memory-utilization 0.7 --max-model-len 16384
#
# TTS_IMAGE=ghcr.io/coqui-ai/xtts-streaming-server:latest-cuda121
# TTS_CONTAINER_PORT=8000
# TTS_HOST_PORT=8001
# TTS_API_PATH=/tts_stream
# TTS_LANGUAGE=en
# TTS_VOICE=Claribel Dervla
# TTS_START_COMMAND=uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

# === END ===
#
# Notes:
# - vLLM AWQ kernel needs compute capability ≥ 7.5 (Turing+). T4 = 7.5 OK,
#   but performance is poor; for T4 prefer the `low` profile with llama.cpp.
# - Piper voices: https://github.com/rhasspy/piper/blob/master/VOICES.md
# - XTTS speakers: see xtts-streaming-server `/studio_speakers` endpoint.
# - LLAMACPP_URL / TTS_BASE_URL in spooknix/.env override these host:port pairs
#   if you proxy through localhost.
